ent economists yergins the quest energy security and the remaking of the modern world  continued his history of the global oil industry but also addressed energy security natural gas electric power climate change and the search for renewable sources of energy all of yergins books were drafted in longhand awardsedit  in  the prime minister of india presented dr yergin with “lifetime achievement award” and the us department of energy awarded him the first “james schlesinger medal for energy security” in  the university of pennsylvania presented him with the first carnot prize for “distinguished contributions to energy policy” peak oil controversyedit yergin has criticized predictions of imminent peak oil noting in  that the early st century is the fifth period of widespread predictions that world oil production was about to fall the four previous times when experts commonly predicted that oil production would soon decrease were first in the s then after each of the world wars and again in the s he wrote that hubbert peak theory ignores the effects of economics and technological advances instead of a peak yergin predicts future oil production will be more of a plateau as increasing prices moderate demand and stimulate production he also addressed peak oil in a chapter in the quest entitled “is the world running out of oil” yergins skepticism toward peak oil has in turn been criticized by the theorys defenders for example jean laherrère contended in  that yergins predictions on energy production and prices omitted key facts leading yergin to draw incorrect conclusions another industry observer criticized yergins statement in september  that the price of crude oil was then higher than justified by fundamentals at the time of yergins statement the price of west texas intermediate oil was us per barrel the price peaked nine months later at us per barrel before dropping dramatically to us in the  financial crisis and fluctuating widely in subsequent years books by daniel yerginedit shattered peace the origins of the cold war and the national security state new york houghton mifflin  reprints penguin   isbn x penguin rev  updated  isbn  the prize the epic quest for oil money and power new york simon  schuster  isbn  reprint simon  schuster  isbn  the quest energy security and the remaking of the modern world penguin press  isbn  books coauthored by daniel yerginedit energy future the report of the energy project at the harvard business school new york random house  isbn  reprints ballantine books isbn  knopf rd ed  isbn  random house new revised rd ed  with robert b stobaugh global insecurity a strategy for energy and economic renewal new york houghton mifflin  isbn  reprint viking penguin books  isbn  with martin hillenbrand russia  and what it means for the world new york random house  isbn  reprint vintage  isbn  with thane gustafson the commanding heights the battle for the world economy revised retitled and updated ed new york free press  isbn x original edition entitled the commanding heights the battle between government and the marketplace that is remaking the modern world new york simon  schuster  isbn  with joseph a stanislaw referencesedit  redburn tom energy future goes beyond ivory tower los angeles times august   retrieved december   fifteen years ago daniel yergin left beverly hills high school to attend yale university and except for summer jobs and brief visits he hasnt been back here since  dan yergin at ihs investor day  slide  at  investorihscom retrieved    a b ringle ken april   daniel yergin turning a prophet how a historian became a market guru and hit the jackpot the washington post retrieved march     ihs executives ihs inc retrieved march     bryan bob  dec  trump is forming an economic advisory team with the ceos of disney general motors jpmorgan and more business insider retrieved  june    klemesrud judy november   energy future the new york times retrieved march      pulitzer prize winners and their works 