more  ihs markit’s yergin on us energy policies more  daniel yergin  wikipedia daniel yergin from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search daniel yergin at the world economic forum annual meeting  born  february   age  los angeles california us residence washington dc alma mater yale university trinity college cambridge occupation author energy analyst awards pulitzer prize website wwwdanielyergincom daniel howard yergin born february   is a pulitzer prizewinning american author speaker and economic researcher yergin is the cofounder and chairman of the cambridge energy research associates an energy research consultancy that is now part of ihs markit inc he is best known as author of the prize the epic quest for oil money and power  and the quest energy security and the remaking of the modern world  he received his phd from cambridge university as a marshall scholar contents  early life and education  career  books  awards  peak oil controversy  books by daniel yergin  books coauthored by daniel yergin  references  articles and interviews  external links early life and educationedit born in los angeles california to a chicago tribune reporter father and a mother who was a sculptor and painter yergin attended beverly hills high school he received his ba from yale university in  where he served on the board of the yale daily news and was a founder of the new journal he earned his phd in international relations  from cambridge university where he was a marshall scholar he has honorary doctorates from colorado school of mines university of houston and the university of missouri careeredit from  through  he was a lecturer at the harvard business school and until  a lecturer at harvards kennedy school of government he founded cambridge energy research associates cera in  with the purchase of a  file cabinet from the salvation armynot specific enough to verify in  cera was acquired by the information company ihs inc of which he is now vice chairman in december  yergin joined a business forum assembled by then presidentelect donald trump to provide strategic and policy advice on economic issues booksedit yergins first book shattered peace the origins of the cold war and the national security state  partly based upon his phd dissertation focused on the origins of the cold war it was named best book of the year by the national historical society he coauthored and coedited with robert b stobaugh energy future the report of the energy project at the harvard business school  which was a new york times bestseller external video booknotes interview with yergin on the prize cspan yergin is best known for the prize the epic quest for oil money and power  a numberone bestseller that won the pulitzer prize for general nonfiction in  and the eccles prize for the best book on economics for a general audience the book was adapted into a pbsbbc miniseries seen by more than  million viewerscitation needed yergin was awarded the  united states energy award for lifelong achievements in energy and the promotion of international understanding” his next book was russia  and what it means for the world  written with thane gustafson which provided scenarios for the development of russia after the collapse of the soviet union this was followed by the commanding heights the battle for the world economy  written with joseph stanislaw which started out as a word essay and described in narrative form the struggle over the frontier between governments and markets and the rise of globalization it was made into a prizewinning sixhour pbsbbc television series yergin was executive producer and host of the series yergin interviewed many highprofile people including bill clinton dick cheney gordon brown newt gingrich and robert rubin as well as prominent economists yergins the quest energy security and the remaking of the modern world  continued his history of the global oil industry but also addressed energy security natural gas electric power climate change and the search for renewable sources of energy all of yergins books were drafted in longhand awardsedit  in  the prime minister of india presented dr yergin with “lifetime achievement award” and the us department of energy awarded him the first “james schlesinger medal for energy security” in  the university of pennsylvania presented him with the first carnot prize for “distinguished contributions to energy policy” peak oil controversyedit yergin has criticized predictions of imminent peak oil noting in  that the early st century is the fifth period of widespread predictions that world oil production was about to fall the four previous times when experts commonly predicted that oil production would soon decrease were first in the s then after each of the world wars and again in the s he wrote that hubbert peak theory ignores the effects of economics and technological advances instead of a peak yergin predicts future oil production will be more of a plateau as increasing prices moderate demand and stimulate production he also addressed peak oil in a chapter in the quest entitled “is the world running out of oil” yergins skepticism toward peak oil has in turn been criticized by the theorys defenders for example jean laherrère contended in  that yergins predictions on energy production and prices omitted key facts leading yergin to draw incorrect conclusions another industry observer criticized yergins statement in september  that the price of crude oil was then higher than justified by fundamentals at the time of yergins statement the price of west texas intermediate oil was us per barrel the price peaked nine months later at us per barrel before dropping dramatically to us in the  financial crisis and fluctuating widely in subsequent years books by daniel yerginedit shattered peace the origins of the cold war and the national security state new york houghton mifflin  reprints penguin   isbn x penguin rev  updated  isbn  the prize the epic quest for oil money and power new york simon  schuster  isbn  reprint simon  schuster  isbn  the quest energy security and the remaking of the modern world penguin press  isbn  books coauthored by daniel yerginedit energy future the report of the energy project at the harvard business school new york random house  isbn  reprints ballantine books isbn  knopf rd ed  isbn  random house new revised rd ed  with robert b stobaugh global insecurity a strategy for energy and economic renewal new york houghton mifflin  isbn  reprint viking penguin books  isbn  with martin hillenbrand russia  and what it means for the world new york random house  isbn  reprint vintage  isbn  with thane gustafson the commanding heights the battle for the world economy revised retitled and updated ed new york free press  isbn x original edition entitled the commanding heights the battle between government and the marketplace that is remaking the modern world new york simon  schuster  isbn  with joseph a stanislaw referencesedit  redburn tom energy future goes beyond ivory tower los angeles times august   retrieved december   fifteen years ago daniel yergin left beverly hills high school to attend yale university and except for summer jobs and brief visits he hasnt been back here since  dan yergin at ihs investor day  slide  at  investorihscom retrieved    a b ringle ken april   daniel yergin turning a prophet how a historian became a market guru and hit the jackpot the washington post retrieved march     ihs executives ihs inc retrieved march     bryan bob  dec  trump is forming an economic advisory team with the ceos of disney general motors jpmorgan and more business insider retrieved  june    klemesrud judy november   energy future the new york times retrieved march      pulitzer prize winners and their works in journalism and the arts the new york times april   retrieved march     cohen joel e april   what will it take to save the earth the new york review of books   khan chris october   yergin only politics c